<subSubSection id="48D355CA8F23FEAD48A75531FE2BFBF9" pageId="365" pageNumber="366" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418F23FEAD48A75531FA24FC15" blockId="365.[151,1436,541,1178]" pageId="365" pageNumber="366">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F23FEAD48A75531FE3CFDC6" bold="true" box="[151,409,541,566]" pageId="365" pageNumber="366">Description of female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F23FEAD499B5531FD8CFDC5" box="[427,553,541,565]" captionStart="PLATE 112" captionStartId="366.[151,233,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[330,1244,184,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-44@366.[294,1293,155,1955]" captionTargetPageId="366" captionText="PLATE 112. Gonatopus capillus, holotype (from Xu &amp; He, 1998d). A. Dorsal view. Length 5.0 mm. B. Chela. Scale bar 0.26 mm for B." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278768" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278768/files/figure.png" pageId="365" pageNumber="366">Plate 112A</figureCitation>
). Apterous; length 5.0 mm. Head black, except mandible testaceous; antenna black, except segment 1 partly testaceous and partly brown and segment 10 yellow-whitish; mesosoma, petiole, metasoma and legs black. Body completely covered with long hairs (as in some species of 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28F23FEAD4CEE5549FF48FD51" authority="Kieffer" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1909" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Trichogonatopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="365" pageNumber="366" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F23FEAD4CEE5549FA39FD8D" box="[1246,1436,613,637]" italics="true" pageId="365" pageNumber="366">Trichogonatopus</emphasis>
Kieffer
</taxonomicName>
). Antenna clavate; antennal segments in following proportions: 6:3.6:14.5:9:8.5:8:6:6:6:8. Head shiny, smooth, unsculptured, except ocellar region granulated; frontal line incomplete; occipital carina absent; temple absent; POL = 1; OL = 0.5; OOL = 5. Palpal formula 4/2. Pronotum crossed by strong transverse impression, shiny, smooth, unsculptured. Scutum and metanotum without lateral pointed apophyses. Metanotum flat, not hollow behind scutellum. Metathorax + propodeum with anterior region smooth, disc reticulate rugose and posterior region transversely striate; anterior region and disc with track of long median longitudinal furrow. Mesopleura and metapleura transversely striate. Meso-metapleural suture almost completely absent, only present on sides of metanotum. Fore tarsal segments in following proportions: 10:1.5:3:10:15.5. Segment 3 of protarsus produced into hook. Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F23FEAD49AC5485FDB9FC31" box="[412,540,937,961]" captionStart="PLATE 112" captionStartId="366.[151,233,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[330,1244,184,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-44@366.[294,1293,155,1955]" captionTargetPageId="366" captionText="PLATE 112. Gonatopus capillus, holotype (from Xu &amp; He, 1998d). A. Dorsal view. Length 5.0 mm. B. Chela. Scale bar 0.26 mm for B." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278768" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278768/files/figure.png" pageId="365" pageNumber="366">Plate 112B</figureCitation>
) with one large subapical tooth and one row of 15 lamellae. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F23FEAD493E54E1FE2CFC15" box="[270,393,973,997]" captionStart="PLATE 112" captionStartId="366.[151,233,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[330,1244,184,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-44@366.[294,1293,155,1955]" captionTargetPageId="366" captionText="PLATE 112. Gonatopus capillus, holotype (from Xu &amp; He, 1998d). A. Dorsal view. Length 5.0 mm. B. Chela. Scale bar 0.26 mm for B." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278768" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278768/files/figure.png" pageId="365" pageNumber="366">Plate 112B</figureCitation>
) with two rows of 12 + 14 lamellae; distal apex with about 15 lamellae. Tibial spurs 1/0/1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418F23FEAD48F754DDFE2BFBF9" blockId="365.[151,1436,541,1178]" box="[199,398,1009,1033]" pageId="365" pageNumber="366">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F23FEAD48F754DDFEAEFBF9" bold="true" box="[199,267,1009,1033]" pageId="365" pageNumber="366">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
